<p class='vspace'><a name='conditionals' id='conditionals'></a>
</p><h3>Use page text variables in <a class='wikilink' href='https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/~monteil/hebergement/wiki_calin/pmwiki/index.php/PmWiki/ConditionalMarkup'>conditional markup</a></h3>
<p>Page text variables will be assigned/evaluated <strong>before</strong> any conditional markup is evaluated. This effectively means that you cannot declare a PTV within an if&hellip;else condition; and also that a PTV will have a value even if it is set within a <code class='escaped'>(:if false:)....(:if:)</code> condition.
</p>
<p class='vspace'><a name='withincode' id='withincode'></a>
</p><h3>Usage - from within code (developers only)</h3>
<p>The standard <code>PageVar({$pagename,$}varname)</code> function can return page text variables, but remember to include the dollar and colon like this:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><div class='indent'><code>{$var=PageVar($}pagename,&rsquo;$:City&rsquo;)</code>
</div><p class='vspace'>It works by caching all page (text) variables it finds in a page (in <code>&#36;PCache</code>) and returns the one requested.
 
</p><div style='clear:right; float:right; font-size:smaller; background-color:#eee;' >
